  "answer": "Step 1: Start with the loan contract equation provided:\\\\\\n\\[ [1-F(\\overline{\\omega}^{j})]\\overline{\\omega}^{j} + (1-\\mu)\\int_{0}^{\\overline{\\omega}^{j}} \\omega R_{t+1}^{k} Q_{t} K_{t+1}^{j} dF(\\omega) = R_{t+1} (Q_{t} K_{t+1}^{j} - N_{t+1}^{j}) \\\\\\\\ \\\\\\nStep 2: Expand the integral term to isolate terms involving $K_{t+1}^{j}$:\\\\\\\\n\\[ [1-F(\\overline{\\omega}^{j})]\\overline{\\omega}^{j} + (1-\\mu) R_{t+1}^{k} Q_{t} K_{t+1}^{j} \\int_{0}^{\\overline{\\omega}^{j}} \\omega dF(\\omega) = R_{t+1} Q_{t} K_{t+1}^{j} - R_{t+1} N_{t+1}^{j} \\\\\\\\ \\\\\\nStep 3: Recognize that $\\int_{0}^{\\overline{\\omega}^{j}} \\omega dF(\\omega)$ represents the expected value of $\\omega$, denoted as $E[\\omega]$. Substitute this into the equation:\\\\\\\\n\\[ [1-F(\\overline{\\omega}^{j})]\\overline{\\omega}^{j} + (1-\\mu) R_{t+1}^{k} Q_{t} K_{t+1}^{j} E[\\omega] = R_{t+1} Q_{t} K_{t+1}^{j} - R_{t+1} N_{t+1}^{j} \\\\\\\\ \\\\\\nStep 4: Rearrange the equation to solve for $K_{t+1}^{j}$:\\\\\\\\n\\[ R_{t+1} Q_{t} K_{t+1}^{j} - (1-\\mu) R_{t+1}^{k} Q_{t} K_{t+1}^{j} E[\\omega] = [1-F(\\overline{\\omega}^{j})]\\overline{\\omega}^{j} + R_{t+1} N_{t+1}^{j} \\\\\\\\ \\\\\\nStep 5: Factor out $Q_{t} K_{t+1}^{j}$ on the left-hand side:\\\\\\\\n\\[ Q_{t} K_{t+1}^{j} [R_{t+1} - (1-\\mu) R_{t+1}^{k} E[\\omega]] = [1-F(\\overline{\\omega}^{j})]\\overline{\\omega}^{j} + R_{t+1} N_{t+1}^{j} \\\\\\\\ \\\\\\nStep 6: Solve for $K_{t+1}^{j}$ by dividing both sides by $Q_{t} [R_{t+1} - (1-\\mu) R_{t+1}^{k} E[\\omega]]$:\\\\\\\\n\\[ K_{t+1}^{j} = \\frac{[1-F(\\overline{\\omega}^{j})]\\overline{\\omega}^{j} + R_{t+1} N_{t+1}^{j}}{Q_{t} [R_{t+1} - (1-\\mu) R_{t+1}^{k} E[\\omega]]} \\\\\\\\[\\nThus, the entrepreneur's demand for capital $K_{t+1}^{j}$ is derived as a function of net worth $N_{t+1}^{j}$, the external finance premium $(1-\\mu)$, and the expected return on capital $E[\\omega]$."
}

